I did some more work on this, excluding rouge sections and pages and tweaking the priorities:

Basically the priorities are assigned as follows, it's not perfect and tweaking one way seemed to end up effecting other sections inversely.

The biggest change was boosting any page with an SEO path to 0.8 on the assumption that those are the pages you want to highlight most as your key pages.

Feel free to feedback though, I think this is probably something we could (and maybe should) endlessly tweak !

Jamie

	 // For Index pages:
 if (depth == 1) {
 priority = 0.7;
 } else if (depth == 2) {
 priority = 0.7;
 } else if (depth == 3) {
 priority = 0.6;
 } else {
 priority = 0.5;
 }

	 // For normal pages:
	 if (depth == 1) {
 priority = 0.6;
 } else if (depth == 2) {
 priority = 0.4;
 } else if (depth == 3) {
 priority = 0.4;
 } else if (depth == 4) {
 priority = 0.4;
 } else {
 priority = 0.3;
 }

 // key sections
 if (p.section == 'Venues') { priority = 0.75 };
 if (p.section == 'Olympic sports') { priority = 0.75 };
 if (p.section == 'Locations of venues') { priority = 0.7 };
 if (p.section == 'Video transcripts') { priority = 0.3 };

 // key pages
 if (p.path == 'index.php') { priority = 0.9 };

 // if the page has a dedicated SEOpath it must be important so boost it
 if (p.path != p.seoPath) { priority = 0.8 };
